import numpy as np # linear algebra
import pandas as pd # data processing, CSV file I/O (e.g. pd.read_csv)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from matplotlib.font_manager import FontProperties
import textwrap as twp
import seaborn as sns

# Set modern styling for all plots
plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')
sns.set_palette("colorblind")  # Use a colorblind-friendly palette
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'sans-serif'
plt.rcParams['font.sans-serif'] = ['Arial', 'DejaVu Sans', 'Liberation Sans']
plt.rcParams['axes.labelsize'] = 12
plt.rcParams['axes.titlesize'] = 14
plt.rcParams['figure.titlesize'] = 16

# Custom color palette for the plots
country_colors = {
    'China': '#1f77b4',
    'India': '#ff7f0e',
    'United States': '#2ca02c',
    'Indonesia': '#d62728',
    'Pakistan': '#9467bd',
    'Brazil': '#8c564b',
    'Nigeria': '#e377c2',
    'Bangladesh': '#7f7f7f',
    'Russia': '#bcbd22',
    'Mexico': '#17becf',
    'Japan': '#aec7e8',
    'Iran': '#ffbb78',
    'Germany': '#98df8a',
    'Canada': '#ff9896',
    'Saudi Arabia': '#c5b0d5',
    'South Korea': '#c49c94'
}

# Load the dataset
df = pd.read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/owid/energy-data/master/owid-energy-data.csv")

# Separate countries and regions
countries_list = df[~df['iso_code'].isna() == True ]['country'].unique().tolist()
main_regions_list = ['Asia', 'Africa', 'North America', 'South America', 'Antarctica', 'Europe', 'Australia']

df_regions = df[df['country'].isin(main_regions_list)]
df = df[df['country'].isin(countries_list)]

# Filter years
df = df[df['year']>1950]

# Find the latest year with complete data for all metrics
required_columns = ['population', 'primary_energy_consumption', 'fossil_fuel_consumption', 
                    'electricity_demand', 'fossil_energy_per_capita']
latest_years = {}

for col in required_columns:
    # Get the years where data exists for this column
    years_with_data = df[df[col].notna()]['year'].unique()
    if len(years_with_data) > 0:
        latest_years[col] = int(max(years_with_data))

# Find the most recent year that has data for all required columns
LATEST_YEAR = min(latest_years.values())
print(f"Latest year with complete data: {LATEST_YEAR}")
print(f"Latest available year per metric: {latest_years}")

# Percentage of total per year calculation
df['population_pct'] = df['population'] / df.groupby('year')['population'].transform('sum')*100
df['primary_energy_consumption_pct'] = df['primary_energy_consumption'] / df.groupby('year')['primary_energy_consumption'].transform('sum')*100
df['fossil_fuel_consumption_pct'] = df['fossil_fuel_consumption'] / df.groupby('year')['fossil_fuel_consumption'].transform('sum')*100
df['electricity_demand_pct'] = df['electricity_demand'] / df.groupby('year')['electricity_demand'].transform('sum')*100

df_regions['population_pct'] = df_regions['population'] / df_regions.groupby('year')['population'].transform('sum')*100
df_regions['primary_energy_consumption_pct'] = df_regions['primary_energy_consumption'] / df_regions.groupby('year')['primary_energy_consumption'].transform('sum')*100
df_regions['fossil_fuel_consumption_pct'] = df_regions['fossil_fuel_consumption'] / df_regions.groupby('year')['fossil_fuel_consumption'].transform('sum')*100
df_regions['electricity_demand_pct'] = df_regions['electricity_demand'] / df_regions.groupby('year')['electricity_demand'].transform('sum')*100

# Per capita calculation
df['primary_energy_consumption_per_capita'] = df['primary_energy_consumption'] / df['population']
df['electricity_demand_per_capita'] = df['electricity_demand'] / df['population']
df_regions['primary_energy_consumption_per_capita'] = df_regions['primary_energy_consumption'] / df_regions['population']
df_regions['electricity_demand_per_capita'] = df_regions['electricity_demand'] / df_regions['population']

# Create top 10 lists using the latest year with complete data
top_10_population_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'population')['country'].to_list()
top_10_primary_energy_consumption_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'primary_energy_consumption')['country'].to_list()
top_10_primary_energy_consumption_pc_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'primary_energy_consumption_per_capita')['country'].to_list()
top_10_fossil_fuel_consumption_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'fossil_fuel_consumption')['country'].to_list()
top_10_fossil_fuel_consumption_pc_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'fossil_fuel_consumption_pct')['country'].to_list()
top_5_fossil_energy_consumption_pc_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(5, 'fossil_energy_per_capita')['country'].to_list()
top_10_electricity_demand_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'electricity_demand')['country'].to_list()
top_10_electricity_demand_pc_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(10, 'electricity_demand_per_capita')['country'].to_list()
top_5_electricity_demand_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(5, 'electricity_demand')['country'].to_list()
top_5_electricity_demand_pc_list = df[df['year']==LATEST_YEAR].nlargest(5, 'electricity_demand_per_capita')['country'].to_list()

# Create a function for styling tables
def style_table(table, highlight_rows=[0, -1]):
    """Apply consistent styling to tables"""
    table.auto_set_font_size(False)
    table.set_fontsize(10)
    table.scale(1, 2)
    
    # Apply custom coloring
    for (row, col), cell in table.get_celld().items():
        if row in highlight_rows:
            cell.set_text_props(fontproperties=FontProperties(weight='bold'), color='white')
            cell.set_facecolor('#3949ab')
        elif row % 2 == 0:
            cell.set_facecolor('#f5f5f5')
        else:
            cell.set_facecolor('#e1e1e1')
            
        # Add borders
        cell.set_edgecolor('#333333')

# Format function for y-axis
@ticker.FuncFormatter
def billion_formatter(x, pos):
    return "%.1f B" % (x/1E9)

# Create figure with enhanced styling
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(15, 12), gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [3, 1]})
fig.suptitle(f'Population Development in Top 10 Countries by Population (1950-{LATEST_YEAR})', 
             fontweight='bold', fontsize=18, y=0.98)

# Adding a subtle background color
fig.patch.set_facecolor('#f8f9fa')

# Plot the population trends with improved styling
for i, entity in enumerate(top_10_population_list):
    color = country_colors.get(entity, sns.color_palette()[i % 10])
    data = df[df['country']==entity]
    ax1.plot(data['year'], data['population'], 
             label=entity, linewidth=2.5, color=color, 
             marker='o', markevery=10, markersize=5)

# Add highlighting for recent years (last 12 years)
ax1.axvspan(LATEST_YEAR-12, LATEST_YEAR, color='#f5f5f5', alpha=0.3)

# Improve axis formatting
ax1.yaxis.set_major_formatter(billion_formatter)
ax1.set_ylabel('Population (billions)', fontweight='bold')
ax1.set_xlabel('Year', fontweight='bold')
ax1.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)

# Add annotations for the most recent data points
for entity in top_10_population_list[:3]:  # Annotate only top 3 for clarity
    data = df[(df['country']==entity) & (df['year']==LATEST_YEAR)]
    if not data.empty:
        x = data['year'].values[0]
        y = data['population'].values[0]
        ax1.annotate(f"{entity}: {y/1E9:.2f}B", 
                    xy=(x, y), xytext=(10, 0), 
                    textcoords="offset points", 
                    fontsize=9, fontweight='bold',
                    arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', connectionstyle='arc3,rad=0.2'))

# Enhance legend
ax1.legend(loc="upper left", frameon=True, fancybox=True, shadow=True, fontsize=10)

# Prepare data for the table
df_top_population = df.query(f'(year in [{LATEST_YEAR}])').nlargest(10, 'population').sort_values(by=['population'], ascending=False)
df_top_population.loc['Total',:] = df_top_population.sum(axis=0)
df_top_population['population'] = pd.to_numeric(df_top_population['population'])
df_top_population['population'] = df_top_population['population'] / 1000000000
df_top_population.loc[df_top_population.index[-1], 'country'] = 'Total'
df_top_population = df_top_population.round(2)

# Create table with improved styling
the_table = ax2.table(cellText=df_top_population[['country','population','population_pct']].values, 
                     cellLoc='center', 
                     colLabels=['Country', 'Population (billions)', 'Percentage of World Population (%)'], 
                     loc='center')
style_table(the_table)

ax2.axis('off')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.92)

# Improve visual hierarchy
for spine in ax1.spines.values():
    spine.set_linewidth(1.5)
    
# Add a title for the table section
plt.figtext(0.5, 0.48, f'Data for {LATEST_YEAR}', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', ha='center')

# Add a footnote
plt.figtext(0.5, 0.01, 'Data source: Our World in Data (OWID)', 
           ha='center', fontsize=8, style='italic')

# Define persian_gulf_palette since it's used in the annotation below but wasn't defined earlier
persian_gulf_palette = sns.color_palette("YlOrRd", n_colors=6)

# Add regional labels for clarity
# Get max value for annotation position
max_fossil_per_capita = df[df['country'].isin(top_10_fossil_fuel_consumption_pc_list)]['fossil_energy_per_capita'].max()

ax1.annotate('Persian Gulf Countries', xy=(1980, max_fossil_per_capita*0.9),
            xytext=(1980, max_fossil_per_capita*0.9),
            fontsize=12, fontweight='bold', color=persian_gulf_palette[2])
